## Flutter Usage

Selection-shaped list query in Flutter or Riverpod:

```dart
{% if sample_model %}final {{ provider_prefix }}{{ sample_model.model_name }}ListProvider = FutureProvider((ref) async {
  final client = ref.watch({{ provider_prefix }}ClientProvider);
  final selection = {{ sample_model.model_name }}Selection()
{% if sample_model.first_field %}    ..{{ sample_model.first_field.value }}()
{% endif %}{% if sample_model.first_include %}    ..{{ sample_model.first_include.value }}()
{% endif %};

  return client.{{ sample_model.accessor }}.list(
    query: selection.toListQuery(
      sort: '-id',
      limit: 20,
      where: 'published=true',
    ),
  );
});
{% else %}final itemsProvider = FutureProvider((ref) async {
  throw UnimplementedError();
});
{% endif %}
```

Projection-backed detail query in Flutter or Riverpod:

```dart
{% if sample_model %}final {{ provider_prefix }}{{ sample_model.model_name }}CardProvider = FutureProvider.family((ref, int id) async {
  final client = ref.watch({{ provider_prefix }}ClientProvider);
  final selection = {{ sample_model.model_name }}Selection()
{% if sample_model.first_field %}    ..{{ sample_model.first_field.value }}()
{% endif %}{% if sample_model.first_include %}    ..{{ sample_model.first_include.value }}()
{% endif %};

  return client.{{ sample_model.accessor }}.getView(
    id,
    projection: selection.asProjection(),
  );
});
{% else %}final itemProvider = FutureProvider.family((ref, int id) async {
  throw UnimplementedError();
});
{% endif %}
```

Rule of thumb:

- use `selection.toListQuery(...)` when the screen still wants full generated model types back from `list(...)` or `get(...)`
- use `selection.asProjection()` with `getView(...)` or `listView(...)` when the screen only needs a shaped payload and should receive a projected wrapper type
